OL,3,CMother wants extra support for parents
OL,4,Cof children with autism
OL,6,F"You're pre-empting all the time, what
OL,7,Fis going to set them off (the
OL,8,Fchildren) and how you can react to it,
OL,9,Fhow you can diffuse the situation."
OL,11,FHowever, Antonia adds that "meeting
OL,12,Fother people in the same boat as you
OL,13,Fis so lovely" when asked about the
OL,14,Fimpact the group was having on her.
OL,16,FIt now has 450 members with events
OL,17,Forganised for neurodiverse children to
OL,18,Fensure they do not miss out on social
OL,19,Factivities that they may not otherwise
OL,20,Fbe able to take part in due to their
OL,21,Fcondition.
